the Java properties format for parsing into the translation memory =20
tool that I use: OmegaT.

OmegaT does not support Latex, so I am trying to think of a way to =20
create a "pseudo" parser for such files.

If there are ways to round-trip Latex to some xml format then I could =20=

easily adapt the source to create a proper filter, based on the xhtml =20=

filter that already exists (I did that for DocBook or WordML/ExcelML =20
files already).

So basically, my first challenge is to find a way to have OmegaT =20
parse the source files. Then comes the translation, and since 1) I am =20=

not an axiom user 2) I do have 2 kids to feed with "real" =20
deadlines :) I will appreciate support here...

Considering the scope of the translation, I'd say that getting the UI =20=

into French should not take more that a few days of work-I mean with =20
final editing/proofreading. As far as the doc is concerned, it will =20
take time so we'd better find a technically satisfying way of doing =20
that right now :)

