Hello,=20

In the interpreter I have this single line :

fct (n, x) =3D=3D eval (real ((c + %i * s)^n), [c, s], [cos x, sin x])

I want to add this function in manip.spad... :-(

So I add theses macros :

  CI      =3D=3D> Complex Integer
  LV      =3D=3D> OrderedVariableList [c,s]
  PCI     =3D=3D> SparseMultivariatePolynomial(Complex Integer, LV)
  PI      =3D=3D> SparseMultivariatePolynomial(Integer, LV)

I add theses variables :

  v1c :=3D ((variable (c))@Union (OrderedVariableList [c,s], "failed"))::LV
  v1s :=3D ((variable (s))@Union (OrderedVariableList [c,s], "failed"))::LV
  vc :=3D v1c :: PCI
  vs :=3D v1s :: PCI
  ve : PCI :=3D vc + (imaginary()::CI) * vs             -- the (c + %i * s)

The interpreter is fine : 8 caracters for the Moivre formula.
I become stupid in front of the compiler : I must type theses 5 lines.=20

And now after hours, axiom reject both=20

  real (ve^n)
  map (t +-> real t, ve^n)

How can I coerce this SMP Complex Integer to SMP Integer ?

How can I use eval from SMP (Integer, [c,s]) to SMP (R, K) ?
where R is the basis Ring of the Expression
  and K are the kernels? functions of Expression.

I hope the end of my program is easier to translate in *.spad.

If someone can help me, again...

the Mupad code for this is :

    if t =3D DOM_INT then
      y :=3D y / n;
      S:=3D genident("S");
      C:=3D genident("C");
      return(subs(expand(((C+I*S)^n-(C-I*S)^n)/2/I),[C=3Dcos(y),S=3Dsin(y)]=
))
    end_if

If possible I prefer use real and imag, and no C+I*S and C-I*S.
But today I can't get any results.

